docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEVIDEO, Nov. 29.--Uruguay's Presidential elections tomorrow will be conducted under circumstances by which it is easily possible that the President of the republic may be chosen by a minority party, casting only 9 per cent of the total votes, with a latent threat of a revolution if this militant minority does not get its way.
